Goel, Ankur wrote:
> 
> Hi,
>        In the crawl logs I am seeing an unknown legend 'P'
> in the discovered URI path. the known legends as per user
> manual are
>     R - Redirect
>     E - Embed
>     X - extracted
>     L - Link
>  
> Can anyone tell me what 'P' means?

Hi, Ankur -

'P' is 'Prerequisite' -- a URI whose scheduling was triggered because it 
was needed before completing another URI (which appears in the 'P' log 
line's 'via' field).

Also, 'X' is specifically for a 'speculative' extraction that is unsure 
of whether the link is more like an 'E'mbed (necessary to render the 
page) or an navigational out'L'ink (an optional path for the viewer to 
follow). 'X's usually come from Javascript or other non-HTML media, and 
are treated as 'E'mbeds to err on the side of inclusion -- but not 
necessarily followed transitively as many hops as a certain 'E'mbed.

I've added a line about 'P' to the user-manual glossary. The updated 
version should appear on the website shortly.

- Gordon @ IA
